(9462, 7592, 1090, 8, 'The Crush', '', '2008-12-02 00:00:00', 0000, 20, 0, 7, 'Verse 1\r\n\r\nYour hand on my shoulder \r\nMakes me shiver deep inside\r\nYou look in my direction makes my face turn red\r\nI smile when you are near me \r\nBut my lips stick too my teeth\r\nI can barely catch my breath to say ‘hello’\r\n\r\nChorus 1\r\n\r\nAll I want to say\r\nIs kiss me\r\nAll I want to say\r\nIs hold me\r\nAll I want to say\r\nIs carry me into the sunset\r\n\r\n\r\nAll I want to say\r\nIs call me\r\nAll I want to say\r\nIs complete me\r\nAll I want to say\r\nIs carry me away\r\n\r\nVerse 2\r\n\r\nSometimes when I daydream\r\nI’ll be naming our first child\r\nAs we both stand there talking about the weather..\r\nWe both agree that February was a little cold\r\nDid you catch me getting lost inside your eyes\r\n\r\nChorus 2\r\n\r\nAll I want to say\r\nIs kiss me\r\nAll I want to say\r\nIs hold me\r\nAll I want to say\r\nIs carry me into the sunset\r\n\r\n\r\nAll I want to say\r\nIs call me\r\nAll I want to say\r\nIs complete me\r\nAll I want to say\r\nIs carry me away\r\n\r\nBridge \r\n\r\nEveryday seems like it could be the day\r\nThat I could finally say\r\nSomething real\r\nEveryday seems like it could be the one\r\nBut when the day is done\r\nI’m still wishing\r\n\r\nChorus 3\r\n\r\nWishing I could say\r\nJust kiss me\r\nWishing I could say\r\nJust hold me\r\nWishing I could say\r\nJust carry me\r\nAway\r\n\r\nAll I want to see \r\nIs call me\r\nAll I want to say is complete me\r\nAll I want to say \r\nIs carry me away', '', 191, '', '', 'A. Coldevin/J. Bryan McCollum', '', '', '', 1, 0, 0, '2008-11-18 13:49:37', '2015-03-12 13:35:11', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(9463, 7592, 1090, 9, 'One NIght Stand', '', '2008-12-02 00:00:00', 0000, 20, 0, 7, 'Verse 1\r\n\r\nAfter four years of loving the wrong man\r\nI try to get along the best that I can\r\nTry to get along but can’t understand\r\nWhat happened..\r\n\r\nAnd the baggage I bring \r\nWhen I step in the ring’s \r\ntoo heavy to think that new love won’t sting\r\ntoo heavy to think about anything – too heavy\r\n\r\nPre chorus 1\r\n\r\nbut I miss the tenderness\r\nthe intimacy of love’s sweet caress\r\nI do pretend that I couldn’t care less\r\nNot in a hurry to start a new mess\r\n\r\nI saw you in the bar\r\nOld friend I’d forgotten about\r\nHigh-school crush that left me in doubt\r\nNow we’re kissing!\r\n\r\nChorus 1\r\n\r\nBut I didn’t get your number\r\nAnd I still wear your smile on my face\r\nYes I didn’t get your number \r\nBut I still wear your smile on my face\r\n\r\nVerse 2\r\n\r\nI still have a lot to do\r\nAnd getting my life back feels really good\r\nYou opened my world up \r\nOne night in may\r\nBut still I just couldn’t ask you to stay\r\n\r\nI guess it wouldn’t be a one night stand\r\nIf I saw you again – if I saw you again\r\nSaw you again\r\nIf I saw you again\r\nIf I saw you\r\n\r\nPre chorus 2\r\n\r\nbut I miss the tenderness\r\nthe intimacy of love’s sweet caress\r\nI do pretend that I couldn’t care less\r\nNot in a hurry to start a new mess\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nI saw you in the bar\r\nOld friend I’d forgotten about\r\nHigh-school crush that left me in doubt\r\nNow we’re kissing!\r\n\r\nChorus 2\r\n\r\nBut I didn’t get your number\r\nAnd I still wear your smile on my face\r\nYes I didn’t get your number \r\nBut I still wear your smile on my face\r\n\r\nBridge\r\n\r\nSunlight in the window\r\nLast nights jeans are on the floor\r\nI don’t really know you\r\nAnd I’m feeling insecure\r\nThere’s no time for coffee\r\nI’m already running late\r\nPick my keys up from the table \r\nMake an innocent escape\r\nSo call me\r\nOr maybe I’ll call you\r\n\r\nChorus 3\r\n\r\nBut I didn’t get your number\r\nAnd I still wear your smile on my face\r\nYes I didn’t get your number \r\nBut I still wear your smile on my face\r\n\r\nBut I didn’t get your number\r\nAnd I still wear your smile on my face\r\nYes I didn’t get your number \r\nBut I still wear your smile on my face', '', 228, '', '', 'A. Coldevin/J. Bryan McCollum', '', '', '', 1, 0, 0, '2008-11-18 13:50:17', '2015-03-12 13:35:11', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
