(9465, 7592, 1090, 11, 'Thank You (For Leaving)', '', '2008-12-02 00:00:00', 0000, 20, 0, 7, 'Intro\r\n\r\nWhen autumn came you broke my heart\r\nThe fire of love just wouldn’t spark\r\nYou left me on the side walk\r\nIn the cold..\r\n\r\nI cried some tears \r\nI drank some beer\r\nI stayed in bed \r\nMy cell phone near\r\nJust praying for a hope in hell to hold\r\n‘till a friend told me\r\njust let him go!\r\n\r\nVerse 1\r\n\r\nI’m finally making time to clean up my room\r\nAnd catch up on books I should read\r\nI got a membership down at the Y\r\nPilates is all that I need\r\nI’m wearing heels for no reason at all\r\nAnd I picked up a new pair of jeans\r\nI’m coming out of the fog I was in\r\nAnd figuring out what it means\r\n\r\nChorus 1\r\n\r\nTo be free\r\nHot\r\nSingle again\r\nThank you for leaving for good\r\nDon’t call \r\nI’ve got enough friends\r\nThank you for leaving for good\r\n\r\nVerse 2\r\n\r\nI’ve got new rules about the way that I date\r\nSo I don’t end up wasting my time\r\nTell me when I look good and don’t show up late\r\nTalk to me and open my mind\r\n\r\nI can’t believe you never offered to pay\r\nWe’d split the bill when we would go out\r\nI’m sure you thought it very modern of you\r\nBut baby cheap is always out\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nChorus 2\r\n\r\nSo glad I’m\r\nFree\r\nHot\r\nSingle again\r\nThank you for leaving for good\r\nDon’t call \r\nI’ve got enough friends\r\nThank you for leaving for good\r\nFree\r\nHot\r\nSingle again\r\nThank you for leaving for good\r\nI’d rather be alone\r\nThan bored with you\r\nThank you for leaving for good\r\n\r\nSo glad I’m\r\nFree\r\nHot\r\nSingle again\r\nThank you for leaving for good\r\nDon’t call \r\nI’ve got enough friends\r\nThank you for leaving for good\r\n\r\nRepeat Chorus', '', 303, '', '', 'A. Coldevin/J. Bryan McCollum', '', '', '', 1, 0, 0, '2008-11-18 13:51:57', '2015-03-12 13:35:11', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(9466, 7592, 1090, 12, 'New Years Kiss', '', '2008-12-02 00:00:00', 0000, 20, 0, 7, 'Verse 1\r\n\r\nI’ve been eating Christmas leftovers for days\r\nFamily’s gone and all the gifts are packed away\r\nAnd in the quiet of my darkened room\r\nAnother year has come and gone too soon\r\nAt least there’s one more night to celebrate\r\n\r\nChorus 1\r\n\r\nSo you raise a glass \r\nAnd you toast the past\r\nAnd you start to reminisce \r\nAnd your friends are there\r\nAnd you know they care\r\nBut still – something’s missing\r\nAs the countdown starts\r\nAll the lonely hearts beat out their midnight wish\r\nMaybe next year I’ll find my new years kiss\r\n\r\nVerse 2\r\n\r\nGonna make my resolutions realistic\r\nCall my mom more often \r\nExercise a little bit\r\nAnd this year I won’t be so shy\r\nI’m gonna hook up with the perfect guy\r\nAnd who knows maybe he’ll be here tonight\r\n\r\nChorus 2\r\n\r\nSo you raise a glass \r\nAnd you toast the past\r\nAnd you start to reminisce \r\nAnd your friends are there\r\nAnd you know they care\r\nBut still – something’s missing\r\nAs the countdown starts\r\nAll the lonely hearts beat out their midnight wish\r\nMaybe next year I’ll find my new years kiss\r\n\r\nVerse 3\r\n\r\nDidn’t have to chase the party \r\nFound the right place\r\nGetting close to midnight when i see a new face\r\nAnd just when his blue eyes meet mine\r\nAnother year is running out of time\r\nI can’t wait to see what next year brings\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nChorus 3\r\n\r\nSo you raise a glass \r\nAnd you toast the past\r\nAnd you start to reminisce \r\nAnd your friends are there\r\nAnd you know they care\r\nBut still – something’s missing\r\nAs the countdown starts\r\nAll the lonely hearts beat out their midnight wish\r\nMaybe next year I’ll find my new years kiss', '', 247, '', '', 'A. Coldevin/J. Bryan McCollum', '', '', '', 1, 0, 0, '2008-11-18 13:52:38', '2015-03-12 13:35:11', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(9467, 7592, 1090, 6, 'It''s So Hard To Say Goodbye', '', '2008-12-02 00:00:00', 0000, 20, 0, 7, 'Intro Chorus \r\n\r\nit’s so hard to say good bye\r\nand when I do I want to cry\r\nbut I’ve got to let you fly\r\nwish this song could make you stay\r\n\r\nVerse 1\r\n\r\n7 months\r\nI heard you say – baby\r\nAs you checked your messages this morning\r\nPack your bags leave it all for a country far away\r\nThe job that you’d been dreaming of was calling\r\n\r\nIt hasn’t been very long\r\nAt least according to my closest friends\r\nWatch your heart take it slow have some fun is all they  say\r\nBut I’m still spending all the time I can\r\nWith you\r\n\r\nChorus 1\r\n\r\nit’s so hard to say good bye\r\nand when I do I want to cry\r\nbut I’ve got to let you fly\r\nwish this song could make you stay\r\n\r\nVerse 2\r\n\r\nfunny how \r\nthis twist of fate\r\ngoes to show that nothing’s ever perfect\r\nhad to kiss a lot of frogs ‘till you finally came along\r\nbut now we don’t have a lot of time to work with\r\n\r\nyou’ll be away for so long\r\nalready writing letters in my head\r\nso we walk and we laugh like we’ll always be together\r\nas we take one step closer to the edge\r\nbut we still pretend\r\n\r\n\r\nChorus 2\r\n\r\nit’s so hard to say good bye\r\nand when I do I want to cry\r\nbut I’ve got to let you fly\r\nwish this song could make you stay\r\n\r\nit’s so hard to say good bye\r\nand when I do I want to cry\r\nbut I’ve got to let you fly\r\nwish this song could make you stay\r\n\r\nRepeat Chorus', '', 231, '', '', 'A. Coldevin/J. Bryan McCollum', '', '', '', 1, 0, 0, '2008-11-18 14:00:24', '2015-03-12 13:35:11', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(9468, 7592, 1090, 7, 'Nothing Compares To You', '', '2008-12-02 00:00:00', 0000, 20, 0, 7, 'it''s been seven hours and fifteen days\r\nSince you took your love away\r\nI go out every night and sleep all day\r\nSince you took your love away\r\nSince you been gone I can do whatever I want\r\nI can see whomever I choose\r\nI can eat my dinner in a fancy restaurant\r\nBut nothing\r\nI said nothing can take away these blues\r\n`Cause nothing compares\r\nNothing compares to you\r\n\r\nIt''s been so lonely without you here\r\nLike a bird without a song\r\nNothing can stop these lonely tears from falling\r\nTell me baby where did I go wrong\r\nI could put my arms around every boy I see\r\nBut they''d only remind me of you\r\nI went to the doctor n''guess what he told me\r\nGuess what he told me\r\nHe said girl u better try to have fun\r\nNo matter what you''ll do\r\nBut he''s a fool\r\n`Cause nothing compares\r\nNothing compares to you\r\n\r\nall the flowers that you planted, mama\r\nIn the back yard\r\nAll died when you went away\r\nI know that living with you baby was sometimes hard\r\nBut I''m willing to give it another try\r\nNothing compares\r\nNothing compares to you\r\nNothing compares\r\nNothing compares to you\r\nNothing compares\r\nNothing compares to you', '', 231, '', '', 'Prince ', '', '', '', 1, 0, 0, '2008-11-18 14:01:05', '2015-03-12 13:35:11', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
