(9474, 7592, 1090, 1, 'Drug Dealer (A Love Song)', '', '2008-12-02 00:00:00', 0000, 20, 0, 7, 'Verse 1\r\n\r\n‘been flirting with you for awhile\r\nI liked your eyes I liked your style\r\nAnd when you said you lked mine too\r\nI thought I could get close to you\r\n\r\nYou called me up and made me laugh\r\nAnd soon we had made dinner plans\r\nWe ate a lot and I got drunk\r\nWe closed the restaurant down\r\nI was thinking is it your place or mine\r\nYou said you didn’t have the time\r\n‘said you had to work but it was already past 2..\r\n\r\nChorus 1\r\n\r\nare you a doctor\r\nare you and artist\r\nare you the man who cleans the streets when I’m in bed?\r\n\r\nAre you a writer\r\nDo you drive a taxi until dawn\r\nOr am I just too naive to know what’s going on?\r\n\r\nVerse 2\r\n\r\nLast Friday I went out with friends \r\nTo hear my favorite dj spin\r\nI danced until my feet got sore\r\nAnd then I saw you on the floor\r\nI asked you to come dance with me\r\nYou said I’d love to but you see\r\nEven though you’re looking fine\r\nI’m working I don’t have the time\r\n\r\nBut you’re not behind the bar\r\nYou’re not bouncing or parking cars\r\nSo tell me what exactly do you do?\r\n\r\nChorus 2\r\n\r\nare you a doctor\r\nare you and artist\r\nare you the man who cleans the streets when I’m in bed?\r\n\r\nAre you a writer\r\nDo you drive a taxi until dawn\r\nOr am I just too naive to know what’s going on?\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nVerse 3\r\n\r\nAt Carol’s party last weekend\r\nI brought you by to meet my friends\r\nWhen we walked in the room went dead\r\nSomeone took me aside and said\r\n\r\nI don’t think he’s your type\r\nHe deals drugs every night\r\nAnd besides that he has a girlfriend or two..\r\n\r\nSo\r\n\r\nChorus 3\r\n\r\nYou’re not a doctor\r\nYou’re not  an artist\r\nYou’re not the man who cleans the streets when I’m in bed?\r\n\r\nYou’re not a writer\r\nYou don’t drive a taxi until dawn\r\nGuess I was too naive to know what’s going on!\r\n\r\nYou’re not a doctor\r\nYou’re not  an artist\r\nYou’re not the man who cleans the streets when I’m in bed?\r\n\r\nYou’re not a writer\r\nYou don’t drive a taxi until dawn\r\nGuess I was too naive to know \r\nThat you’re out there dealing snow\r\nGuess I was too naïve to know\r\nWhat’s going on..', '', 237, '', '', 'A. Coldevin/J. Bryan McCollum', '', '藝見傳播', '', 1, 0, 0, '2008-11-18 14:53:12', '2015-03-12 13:35:11', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(9475, 7592, 1090, 2, 'Booty Call', '', '2008-12-02 00:00:00', 0000, 20, 0, 7, 'Verse 1\r\n\r\nI should have known when you said you liked cats\r\nThat it wouldn’t work out\r\nI met you through a friend of a friend\r\nWhen you came to my house\r\n\r\nYou brought a great bottle to dinner\r\nAnd you laughed at my jokes\r\nAnd when everyone was gone\r\nAnd the candles were low\r\nThat’s when we got real close\r\n\r\nChorus 1\r\n\r\nBooty call – booty call\r\nNo strings no stress \r\nKeep it casual\r\nDoesn’t always have to be so emotional\r\nCan’t we just have some fun\r\n\r\nVerse 2\r\n\r\nIn the past I was a little intense\r\nSo this time I thought I would chill out\r\nIf I had the urge to call everyday\r\nI’d call somebody else\r\nAnd when the whole world is asleep\r\nWell that’s when my phone would ring\r\nYou’d say you were on your way\r\nListen out for the door\r\nAnd my heart would sing\r\n\r\nLa la \r\nChorus 2\r\n\r\nBooty call – booty call\r\nNo strings no stress \r\nKeep it casual\r\nDoesn’t always have to be so emotional\r\nCan’t we just have some fun\r\nBooty call – booty call\r\nNo stress no mess \r\nKeep it casual\r\nDoesn’t always have to be matrimonial\r\nCan’t we just have some fun\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nBridge \r\n\r\nWell you went to see a movie\r\nThat I told you that I wanted to see\r\nWithout me\r\nI gave you my umbrella as you walked out in the rain\r\nAnd you swept me off my feet on Friday night\r\nThen I made omelettes and tea\r\nIn the morning\r\nBut I would hear your sexy voice again\r\nFor ten long days..\r\n\r\nVerse 3\r\n\r\nWell I know you’re not supposed to get hooked\r\nBut it didn’t work out\r\nI guess I’m just attached to the things\r\nThat love is all about\r\nWould it be so wrong to bring me some flowers?\r\nOr get to know my family?\r\nBut when I broke it down to you \r\nYou just started to squirm…\r\nThat was my cue to leave\r\n\r\nYou said – \r\n\r\nChorus 3\r\n\r\nBooty call – booty call\r\nNo strings no stress \r\nKeep it casual\r\nDoesn’t always have to be so emotional\r\nCan’t we just have some fun\r\nBooty call – booty call\r\nNo stress no mess\r\nKeep it casual\r\nDoesn’t always have to be so emotional\r\nWhy can’t I just have fun…', '', 202, '', '', 'A. Coldevin/J. Bryan McCollum', '', '藝見傳播', '', 1, 0, 0, '2008-11-18 14:53:47', '2015-03-12 13:35:11', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(9476, 7592, 1090, 3, 'This Love Is Freeing Me', '', '2008-12-02 00:00:00', 0000, 20, 0, 7, 'Verse 1\r\n\r\nIt seems that living outside\r\nOf the world within my heart\r\nI lost the voice of reason\r\nAnd didn’t know where to start\r\nLooking in to the deep beneath the surface\r\nExamining every part\r\nComing up with the same exhausted answers\r\nAnd taking it all to heart\r\n\r\nChorus 1\r\n\r\nAnd even though I love you\r\nIt all feels new to me\r\nA special place to be\r\nAbandoning the word play\r\nAnd loving easily \r\nThis love is freeing me\r\nAnd even though I love\r\nIt all feels new to me\r\nSpecial place to be \r\nAbandoning the word play\r\nAnd loving easily\r\nThis love is freeing me\r\n\r\nVerse 2\r\n\r\nSometimes I felt real doubtful\r\nThat what we had was true\r\nI wanted to hold tighter\r\nAnd stop letting you be you\r\nFear of losing the vibe we shared together\r\nAnd risking a broken heart\r\nNow I know that our spirits are forever\r\nEven when we’re apart\r\n\r\nChorus 2\r\n\r\nAnd even though I love you\r\nIt all feels new to me\r\nA special place to be\r\nAbandoning the word play\r\nAnd loving easily \r\nThis love is freeing me\r\nAnd even though I love\r\nIt all feels new to me\r\nSpecial place to be \r\nAbandoning the word play\r\nAnd loving easily\r\nThis love is freeing me\r\n\r\nBridge\r\n\r\nIt’s ‘cuz we took the time to know each other\r\nNo thinking of yesterday\r\nBaby we took the time to love one another\r\nAnd see it through all the way\r\n\r\nChorus 3\r\n\r\nAnd even though I love you\r\nIt all feels new to me\r\nA special place to be\r\nAbandoning the word play\r\nAnd loving easily \r\nThis love is freeing me\r\nAnd even though I love\r\nIt all feels new to me\r\nSpecial place to be \r\nAbandoning the word play\r\nAnd loving easily\r\nThis love is freeing me', '', 238, '', '', 'A. Coldevin/J. Bryan McCollum', '', '藝見傳播', '', 1, 0, 0, '2008-11-18 14:54:27', '2015-03-12 13:35:11', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(9477, 7592, 1090, 4, 'On The Day After', '', '2008-12-02 00:00:00', 0000, 20, 0, 7, 'Verse 1\r\n\r\nLove will\r\nGet you through anything\r\nBut a day like today\r\n\r\nTell me\r\nThere’s always more fish in the sea\r\nThis one got away\r\n\r\nWasn’t it wonderful\r\nWasn’t it right from the start\r\nYou stood so close to me\r\nTalking so quietly\r\nAll I could hear was your heart\r\n\r\nChorus 1\r\n\r\nOn the day after\r\nThe coffee tastes bitter\r\nAnd the sunlight’s too bright for my eyes\r\nOn the day after\r\nThe future looks lonely\r\nBut at least now I’m too tired to cry\r\nOn the day after you said goodbye\r\n\r\nVerse 2\r\n\r\nStrange how everything’s  different\r\nBut it still looks the same\r\nThis room\r\nPhotos\r\nAnd t-shirts\r\nAnd dreams\r\nI’ll pack them away\r\n\r\nWas it impossible\r\nWasn’t it worth it to stay\r\nYou meant the world to me\r\nHeld me and promised me\r\nBut was it all just a game\r\n\r\nChorus 2\r\n\r\nOn the day after\r\nThe coffee tastes bitter\r\nAnd the sunlight’s too bright for my eyes\r\nOn the day after\r\nThe future looks lonely\r\nBut at least now I’m too tired to cry\r\nOn the day after you said goodbye\r\n\r\nWas it impossible\r\nWasn’t it right from the start\r\n\r\nYou meant the world to me \r\nHeld me and promised me\r\nAll I could hear was your heart\r\n\r\nChorus 3\r\n\r\nOn the day after\r\nThe coffee tastes bitter\r\nAnd the sunlight’s too bright for my eyes\r\nOn the day after\r\nThe future looks lonely\r\nBut at least now I’m too tired to cry\r\nOn the day after you said goodbye', '', 216, '', '', 'by  A. Coldevin/J. Bryan McCollum', '', '藝見傳播', '', 1, 0, 0, '2008-11-18 14:55:04', '2015-03-12 13:35:11', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(9478, 7592, 1090, 5, 'Day Job', '', '2008-12-02 00:00:00', 0000, 20, 0, 7, 'Verse 1\r\n\r\nWhere did the weekend go \r\nI say to Steve\r\nAs the elevator opens\r\nOn the 7th floor of hell\r\n\r\nThird cup of coffee \r\nNow I’m half awake\r\nStart to wander through my email\r\nGetting cozy in my cell\r\n\r\nPre chorus 1\r\n\r\n1-2-3-4-5 more hours\r\ncrush my soul\r\nand send me flowers\r\ntake me home\r\nwhere I can be myself again\r\n\r\nChorus 1\r\n\r\nSomeday\r\nMonday I’ll sleep in ‘till noon\r\nAnd stay out late\r\nAnd live the life I want\r\nI know\r\nOne day\r\nI’ll leave this dull grey cubicle behind\r\nIf the rent could still be paid\r\n\r\nVerse 2\r\n\r\nTry to be different \r\nWore striped socks today\r\nI think that everybody noticed\r\nHeard them talking in the hall\r\n\r\nHey you know there’s muffins \r\nOn Todd’s desk\r\nWell I better hurry now and get one\r\nGuess I’ll have to miss that call\r\n\r\nPre chorus 2\r\n\r\n1-2-3-4-5 more hours\r\nsing my love songs in the shower\r\nbrush my teeth\r\nand try to plan my\r\ngetaway!\r\n\r\n\r\nChorus 2\r\n\r\nSomeday\r\nMonday I’ll sleep in ‘till noon\r\nAnd stay out late\r\nAnd live the life I want\r\nI know\r\nOne day\r\nI’ll leave this dull grey cubicle behind\r\nIf the rent could still be paid\r\n\r\nBridge\r\n\r\nThe dental plan \r\nServes me well\r\nLove my ergonomic chair\r\nSteady pay\r\nThat I never seem to save\r\nI’ve been wasting too much time\r\nI don’t wanna be there\r\n\r\nChorus 3\r\n\r\nSomeday\r\nMonday I’ll sleep in ‘till noon\r\nAnd stay out late\r\nAnd live the life I want\r\nI know\r\nOne day\r\nI’ll leave this dull grey cubicle behind\r\nThings are gonna be different\r\n\r\nSomeday\r\nMonday I’ll sleep in ‘till noon\r\nAnd stay out late\r\nAnd live the life I want\r\nI know\r\nOne day\r\nI’ll kiss this dull grey cubicle goodbye\r\nIf the rent could still be paid', '', 172, '', '', 'A. Coldevin/J. Bryan McCollum', '', '藝見傳播', '', 1, 0, 0, '2008-11-18 14:55:32', '2015-03-12 13:35:12', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
